<div class='documentTop'><div>
  
  
    <h1>Established companies</h1>
  
  </div></div>
  

  <div class="documentBody" id="Tekstinnhold">   
  <div>
    <p><strong><img alt="" src="/upload/KRD/Temabilder/REGA/etablerte_bedrifter_hoved_540x270.jpg" align="top" /></strong></p>
<p><strong>One essential aspect of the work to facilitate increased added value is measures to increase capacity for and rate of innovation within established companies.</strong> <br /><br />The government aims to stimulate business development by introducing both general and specific policy instruments. The government feels that Innovation Norway plays a particularly important part in funding investments in commerce in the more isolated parts of Norway. <br /><br /><strong>Lower threshold</strong><br />Public policy is not intended to compensate for poor profitability within individual companies or industries, but to lower the threshold for promoting good development projects within companies: both growth companies and companies established in order to create a livelihood. Direct support for companies in the form of loans and subsidies aims at promoting projects that will be profitable once the support period has ended. <br /><br /><strong>Promoting the development of contact networks</strong><br />Not only shall the public bodies provide capital, they shall also promote a more systematic form of contact between companies and various sources of innovation. Contact between suppliers and customers, between companies and R&amp;D groups, is essential for innovation. Another central factor in this context is a good working climate for employees and material for new concepts. Initiatives directly targeting companies and managed by Innovation Norway are primaily financed by funds channelled via the county authorities. In addition, a number of programmes and initiatives are financed by national funds directly from the Ministry of Local Government and Regional Development.<br /></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.innovasjonnorge.no/system/Global-toppmeny/English/">Innovation Norway</a></li>
<li><a href="http://siva.no/internett/cms.nsf/pages/english?open" target="_blank">SIVA - The Industrial Development Corporation of Norway</a> </li>
<li><a href="http://www.forskningsradet.no/en/Home+page/1177315753906" target="_blank">The Research Council of Norway</a></li></ul>
  </div>
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
